      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yeah, the duplication in the ExceptionTriggeredByClient() itself I didn\u0027t like much either.\n\nThe problem is that the thread information needs to be consumed by the exception initialization (because it needs to make the fake exception record to blame a thread) but it also is the place where we learn that we need to modify the suspend counts and have the information required to do so.\n\nSo, for a third attempt: move the exception initialization up higher, and have the exception snapshot use/modify the process reader thread data (rather than the thread snapshot data). I think this is a bit cleaner, in that things only happen in one place, and the thread initialization in ProcessSnapshotWin doesn\u0027t need to know about modified suspend counts.\n\nThe drawback is that ExceptionSnapshotWin::Initialize modifies suspend count, but that seems like the right place to do so because of the use+consume that we need to do here.",
